	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />True, but there's a reason that languages like Fortran were invented. (No, it wasn't to write <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dian_Shi_Mali" class="postlink">PUSH START TO RICH</a>.) For tasks where being able to express complicated logic is more important than user response time, a compiler doesn't have to be 100 percent efficient. That's why so many business rely on Python and/or VB, and why web applications are JavaScript instead of downloadable native clients.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
