	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I personally can't believe that people code in C for the NES. I barely get by penny-pinching with every available cycle when coding in ASM. And I agree with the whole absolute control thing. When coding in C, you just tell it to multiply two non-integer numbers willy-nilly and you don't realize that you're probably doing something that takes a dozen or more scanlines. And without ASM, things like doynax's polygon engine, or tokumaru's raycaster would not be possible.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


